## How to read this list

Each row represents a third-party service we use that may receive or
process PHI or other personal information collected through
{{PROJECT_NAME}}. We are accountable under PHIPA (s. 17, s. 12) and
PIPEDA (Principle 1) for these subprocessors' practices when they
process PHI on our behalf.

| Column | Meaning |
|---|---|
| **Vendor** | Legal name + service. |
| **Data category** | What classes of information the vendor processes (PHI, billing, communications, technical, etc.). |
| **PHI access** | Does the vendor touch PHI directly? (`yes` / `no` / `incidental`). |
| **Region** | Where the vendor processes the data. |
| **DPA / contract** | Data-processing agreement; for PHI-touching vendors, what equivalent of a Business Associate Agreement is in place. |
| **Audit evidence** | SOC 2 Type II, ISO 27001, HITRUST, or other independent attestation. |
| **Notes** | Anything customers should know. |

