## PHI-touching vendor onboarding

Before adding a vendor that will process PHI:

- [ ] Confirm the vendor offers PHIPA-equivalent contractual terms
      (data-processing agreement covering use, disclosure, retention,
      safeguards, subprocessing, breach notification).
- [ ] Confirm independent audit evidence (SOC 2 Type II at minimum;
      HITRUST or ISO 27001 where available).
- [ ] Confirm processing region(s) and whether cross-border processing
      is required.
- [ ] Confirm the vendor's breach-notification SLA matches our
      breach-response runbook.
- [ ] Confirm the vendor's account-deletion / data-return process.
- [ ] Add the vendor to this table.
- [ ] Notify customers per the privacy policy where required.
- [ ] If {{PROJECT_NAME}} is an Agent of a HIC, notify the HIC of the
      new subprocessor before activation.

## Changes

When a subprocessor is added, changed, or removed:

1. Update the table above (and the "Last reviewed" date).
2. Notify active customers per the privacy policy if material.
3. If {{PROJECT_NAME}} is an Agent: notify the HIC.
4. Record the change in the CHANGELOG.

